<TITLE> Parliament sits Sunday afternoon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  Parliament will reconvene at 4pm on Sunday after a two-day recess. The budget session of the ninth parliament began on June 2  with the main opposition BNP walking out of parliament twice and not attending parliament the following day. Finance minister AMA Muhith is set to table the national budget for 2010-11 financial year on June 10. BNP will set out its views and proposals on the budget for the next fiscal year at an event at the Sheraton Hotel on Monday afternoon presided over by Khaleda Zia. Political leaders, economists, businessmen, intellectuals, editors of national dailies, professionals, civil society representatives and envoys of foreign missions have been invited to the programme. 
